    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When removing limit washers, spacers and gears, note their location. Keep internal-splined washers
                    and external-splined spacers with the gear from which they were removed. There is only one limit
                    washer and one spacer belonging to each gear. No external- splined washer under 4th or 2nd.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300795">Figure 95</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300795" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300795" filename="../figg13/g1300795.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Remove Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear spline spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300795">Figure 95</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt mainshaft up, and remove the sliding clutch from the opposite end (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300796">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300796" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300796" filename="../figg13/g1300796.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Remove Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft in a vertical position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300797">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300797" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300797" filename="../figg13/g1300797.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 97. Remove Mainshaft Key Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft key snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300797">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the mainshaft rear, pull the mainshaft key from the mainshaft key way.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the reverse gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300798">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300798" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300798" filename="../figg13/g1300798.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Remove Reverse-1st Speed Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse-1st speed sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300798">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift and turn 1st gear to align the limit washer splines (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300799">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300799" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300799" filename="../figg13/g1300799.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 99. Align Limit Washer Splines</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the limit washer, spacer and 1st gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a0">Figure 100</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007a0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007a0" filename="../figg13/g13007a0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 100. Remove Limit Washer, Spacer and 1st Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the 2nd gear limit washer to align its splines with the mainshaft. Remove 2nd gear and
                its limit washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007a1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007a1" filename="../figg13/g13007a1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 101. Remove 2nd Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd-3rd sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove each remaining gear, limit washer and spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a2">Figure 102</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007a2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007a2" filename="../figg13/g13007a2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 102. Remove Gear, Limit Washer and Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the roll pin; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007a2">Figure 102</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
